Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Marketing and Communications Coordinator - maternity leave contract Barrie , ON Description JOB SUMMARY: Under the direction of the Manager, Marketing and Communications, the Marketing and Communications Coordinator will play an integral role in the library’s brand management. The position takes responsibility for contributing to the library’s internal and external print and digital communications, marketing campaigns, social media and website, videography and photography, and may assist with community relations, events and special projects that support the organization.This is a temporary 12-month maternity leave contract with the possibility of extension to 18 months. Hours are full-time, 35 hours per week with both on-site and remote work opportunities.SUPERVISORY RELATIONSHIPS:Reports to the Manager, Marketing and CommunicationsCollaborates with other members of the marketing teamQUALIFICATIONS:Two- to three-year Diploma or Degree in Marketing, Communications or related fieldTwo to three years’ related experience working in similar role, preferably in a non-profit environmentExcellent oral and written communication skills including meticulous grammar and spellingStrong time management and organizational skills with extreme attention to detailExperience managing social media channels professionally, including content planning and scheduling with HootSuite and Later, creating ads, monitoring analytics and monthly reportingDemonstrated website management experience including content creation and ensuring brand and voice are consistent across the siteExperience creating graphics for digital and print platforms through efficient use of images and a keen eye for designProven computer literacy including all Microsoft applications, e-newsletter marketing with MailChimp, video editing software, survey tools, and graphic design softwareExperience with Adobe Creative Suite is considered an assetStrong aptitude for acquiring new technical skills and knowledgeComplete fluency in English language; ability to speak French is an assetComfortable with public speaking, training and presentingAbility to engage tactfully and professionally with a culturally diverse public community in person and through social media Driver’s license and access to a vehicle is requiredA police check, including Vulnerable Sector Screening, is required and is a condition of employmentTo protect our community and our fellow staff members, Barrie Public Library has implemented a mandatory COVID-19 vaccination policy for all staff, as a condition of employment. All Library staff must be fully vaccinated, unless they have been granted a medical exemption or accommodation under the Ontario Human Rights Code. Proof of fully vaccinated status will be required on the first day of employment. A copy of the Library’s policy is available upon request.DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:Under the direction of the Manager, Marketing and Communications, and within a team culture:Implementing the library’s internal and external marketing and communications via print and digital platforms, including, but not limited to: Social media content creation, planning, scheduling, monitoring, engagement, and evaluation of key metricsWebsite management, including writing and posting news items, updating the home page, and assisting website editorsPhotography and videography to support and promote the library’s services, programs, spaces, and collections. Includes all library locations, off-site events, and off-site collections Email marketing using PatronPoint and MailChimp. Includes planning promotions, working with departments for content, writing, and tracking metricsCreating temporary and modular signage and assisting staff with templates Graphic design for digital screens, social media, website, postcards, bookmarks, and other print piecesIdentifying new opportunities and generating tactics for new memberships and member retentionMaintaining communications and relations with staff across all departments of the organizationMaintaining accurate and up-to date-files including organization of stock and custom photographyAssisting with the execution of events such as the annual Barrie Dragon Boat FestivalPerforms all other duties as required.Those wishing to apply should submit a cover letter and current resume to: Jane LittleManager, Human ResourcesBarrie Public Library60 Worsley StreetBarrie, Ontario L4M 1L6 Fax: 705-728-4322 Email: jobs@barrielibrary.ca Compensation $56,693 - $66,302 Closes: 12 May, 2023 Barrie Public Library Barrie , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
