Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Operations Manager Stratford , ON Description Reporting to the CEO, as a member of the Administration Team, the Operations Manager is responsible for overseeing the technological and physical resources of the Library. These services enable the fundamental components of library service to take place and are of key strategic importance in facilitating the Library’s growth and success. This position acts as the backup to the CEO in their absence and is the second-most senior position in the SPL organizational structure. This position is full-time, and permanent.
Duties and Responsibilities Acts as the Perth County Information Network Administrator: reporting to the Management Committee, manages the Integrated Library System, all software related to the consortium, troubleshooting, statistics, projects, and special requests. Provides remote and on-site technical support to two of the member libraries. Responsible for the flow of materials between PCIN locations. Manages the Information Technology components of SPL Operations: responsible for the strategic direction and operation of the IT services, staff and infrastructure. Ensures the stability, security and scalability of all technology-based systems for staff and the public. Plans, proposes, implements, manages and evaluates technology solutions including network and server infrastructure, computing software licensing, security, email services, file storage and backups, telephone infrastructure, peripherals, business continuity and disaster recovery. Responds to trends, practices, innovations and new technologies which enhance the quality and efficiency of library services. Supervisor of the Technical Services Department: manages the activities and staff of the department responsible for cataloguing and InterLibrary Loan and interfacing with the ILS. Building and facilities management: ensures the physical spaces are safe, attractive and well-maintained; manages projects as they arise in tandem with the City of Stratford. Participates as the management representative on the Joint Health and Safety Committee. Acts as the backup to the CEO and senior leader of the SPL with delegated powers of authority in the absence of the CEO. Resolves customer service problems and empowers public service staff to do the same. Assumes responsibility for maintaining the safety and comfort of the Library; reports issues and incidents to the appropriate personnel. Participates in library committees, external committees/associations, and other work groups to achieve the goals of the Library. Regularly participates in training opportunities and maintains awareness of developments in the field. Shares developments with colleagues when relevant; suggests and incorporates new ideas. Other duties as required.
Formal Qualifications An MLIS degree from an accredited library school or equivalent combination of education and experience Five years’ experience in public libraries and systems, including proven supervisory and management experience Experience successfully overseeing strategic direction for diverse portfolios, managing operations and technological projects Supervisory experience that demonstrates the ability to select, train, motivate and lead staff in a collaborative work environment Experience with setting goals, developing strategic direction, leading planning, directing effective meetings, and creating business cases Excellent interpersonal, leadership, and team skills to support the organizational vision and mission of the library Able to establish, maintain, and promote healthy working relationships with people at all levels inside and outside the library Strong verbal, written communication skills including negotiation skills; report writing and presentation skills Proven project management, planning and change management skills Strong problem identification, troubleshooting and problem resolution skills Demonstrated advanced technical knowledge, including competencies in a wide range of technology applications as they apply to library and information services including: Integrated library systems; familiarity with SirsiDynix Horizon, BlueCloud Analytics and BiblioCommons an asset PC Software, infrastructure, and hardware technology, including networks, servers, DHCP, DNSH, Microsoft 365 Security, back-ups, business continuity Internet and online applications; Drupal an asset Strong understanding of technical services standards and processes including collections management, cataloguing, processing, authority control and interlibrary loan This position requires occasional travel to other library locations within the County of Perth
(ie. Listowel, Mitchell, St Marys, Milverton), candidates must have a reliable mode of transportation A police check, including Vulnerable Sector Screening, is required and is a condition of employment
